I just found out about this forced verification myself after losing access to GPT-5 Thinking without verifying myself.
    LetsKit - [How can I use function calling with response format (structured output feature) for final response?][10]

    I’ve been banging my head against this too, and finally found some relief. I use the API directly, so the above solution didn’t help. 
I originally had "strict": false in my tools. Mainly because each tool had optional properties. Once I set "strict": true and changed all my optional properties to include anyOf[{"type": "string","type": "null"}] I got a massive performance boost in tool calling accuracy.
